raw_markdown: |
  
  ### RVN: Part 3 – Replace Gmail (your email is not private) ✉️
  
  **Narrative:**  
  “Gmail is just convenient and reliable. Everyone uses it.”
  
  **Reality:**
  
  Gmail is one of Google’s most powerful **surveillance tools**.  
  Every email you send or receive is scanned, analyzed, and stored. Google doesn’t just read your mail to show you ads — it builds an extremely detailed profile of you, your contacts, your interests, and your entire life.
  
  This is not a conspiracy theory. This is their business model.
  
  **Better alternatives:**
  
  - **ProtonMail** → Best and easiest choice for most people (end-to-end encrypted, based in Switzerland, no scanning)
  - **Tutanota** → Strong privacy, open source, German
  - **Skiff Mail** (now part of Notion) → Beautiful design with end-to-end encryption
  - **Self-hosted** (Mailcow, Poste.io or similar + custom domain) → Maximum sovereignty (for advanced users)
  
  **Action for today (takes 10-15 minutes):**
  
  1. Create an account at **ProtonMail** → https://proton.me/mail
  2. Set up a new email address (e.g. yourname@proton.me)
  3. Start informing important contacts that you’re switching
  4. Optionally set up forwarding from Gmail temporarily so you don’t miss anything
  
  Bonus tip: Buy your own domain name (via Proton or Namecheap) and link it. Then you’re truly independent.
  
  **OIM Way Out**
  
  Every email you send through Gmail is a voluntary gift to Google.  
  Digital sovereignty means your communication belongs to you again.
  
  This is Part 3.  
  Tomorrow Part 4: Why you should ditch Windows (and switch to Linux).
  
  **Question to you**
  
  Are you still using Gmail as your main account?  
  Or have you already switched? If yes, to what?
  
  Feel free to share your experience below.
  
  #DigitalSovereignty #DumpGmail #ProtonMail #Privacy #OIM
  
